        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1631218169" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12956272802732347474">Listened to this one on audio read by the amazing Tim Curry in a few hours and it made it a whole lot better. I feel like this was a bit of a filler book but I still enjoyed it. I don’t like Fiona (the tiny bit of romance in here was completely unnecessary and icky to me lol I&apos;m not one for romance in MG.). That twist with the hook-handed man was pretty cool and Count Olaf was just as fucked up as he always is. I think I might check out more audio books in the future. I thought they weren’t for </span>
  <span id="freeText12956272802732347474" style="display:none">Listened to this one on audio read by the amazing Tim Curry in a few hours and it made it a whole lot better. I feel like this was a bit of a filler book but I still enjoyed it. I don’t like Fiona (the tiny bit of romance in here was completely unnecessary and icky to me lol I'm not one for romance in MG.). That twist with the hook-handed man was pretty cool and Count Olaf was just as fucked up as he always is. I think I might check out more audio books in the future. I thought they weren’t for me because I’ve tried so many and my attention span is shit but this one worked pretty damn well. Tomorrow I plan on listening to book 12!<br /><br />-	Richard :)<br /></span>
